<common-name datatype='string'>motRAB-cheAW</common-name>
<comment datatype='string'>The CpxR-dependent expression of the &lt;i&gt;motAB-cheAW&lt;/i&gt; operon is diminished under the stress condition caused by the introduction of the R1-16 plasmid, which encodes the type IV secretion system (T4S machinery) in the cell [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16952953&quot;&gt;Zahrl06&lt;/a&gt;].
&lt;p&gt;
The mRNA produced by the  &lt;i&gt; motAB-cheAW &lt;/i&gt; operon has been observed mainly in the poles of the cell [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/31540875&quot;&gt;Kannaiah19&lt;/a&gt;].
&lt;p&gt;
In a study where it was shown that the L-tryptophan eradicated persister cells, it was observed that the exogenous amino acid downregulated the expression of &lt;i&gt; motAB&lt;/i&gt; as well as other flagellar genes [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/31271063&quot;&gt;Li19&lt;/a&gt;].
&lt;p&gt;
The &lt;i&gt;motA&lt;/i&gt; gene is downregulated by long-term (8 to 12 h) exposure of &lt;i&gt;E. coli&lt;/i&gt; to some biocides [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/32385082&quot;&gt;Merchel20&lt;/a&gt;].</comment>
